    <p><strong>The bottom line:</strong> If your kitchen primarily bakes cakes, cookies, and pastries, a convection oven is perfectly adequate and far cheaper. But if your menu includes roasted meats, steamed dishes, multi-course banquet cooking, reheating, or high-volume batch cooking — a combi oven pays for itself through higher cooking yields, labour savings, and the ability to replace 2–3 standalone appliances.</p>

