    <h2>7. Gas vs Electric Combi Ovens</h2>
    <p>This is an important decision for Indian buyers, especially given regional variations in electricity costs and gas availability. See our dedicated <a href="/blog/gas-vs-electric-oven-bakery">Gas vs Electric Oven</a> guide for bakery-specific analysis.</p>

    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Factor</th><th>Electric Combi Oven</th><th>Gas Combi Oven</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Purchase Price</td><td>Standard</td><td>10–20% higher</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Running Cost (India)</td><td>₹8–15/kWh (commercial rates)</td><td>₹40–60/kg LPG; PNG much cheaper</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Monthly Energy Cost (10-tray, 8h/day)</td><td>₹25,000 – ₹45,000</td><td>₹12,000 – ₹25,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Installation</td><td>Needs 3-phase power, proper wiring</td><td>Needs gas lines, safety certifications</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Temperature Precision</td><td>Excellent (±1°C)</td><td>Good (±2–3°C)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Steam Quality</td><td>Excellent</td><td>Good to Excellent</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Availability of Models</td><td>Wide (most brands)</td><td>Limited (fewer models available)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Maintenance</td><td>Simpler (no burner servicing)</td><td>Burner and gas valve maintenance needed</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Safety Approvals</td><td>Standard electrical</td><td>Requires gas safety certificate</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Best For India</td><td>Hotels, cloud kitchens, hospitals</td><td>Large kitchens with PNG connection</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Our recommendation for India:</strong> Electric combi ovens are the default choice for most Indian kitchens. They are easier to install, offer better temperature precision, and have a wider model selection. Gas combi ovens make sense only if you have a piped natural gas (PNG) connection — running a gas combi on LPG cylinders is impractical and potentially hazardous given the gas volumes required. Hotels in cities with PNG infrastructure (Delhi, Mumbai, Ahmedabad, Bangalore) should consider gas models for lower running costs.</p>

